HEADWORD: Fourpence
<hw>Four"pence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
British silver coin, worth four pence; a groat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A name formerly given in New England to the Spanish
half real, a silver coin worth six and a quarter cents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>four-ply</ent>⟦br⟧
